   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOUR CONCERNING THE DIVINE TRINITY 4 Scripture Reading: Col 2:2, 9; Isa 9:6; 2 Cor 3:17; John 1:14; Heb 2:14; Col 1:15, 18; Acts 2:36 OUTLINE The all-inclusiveness of Christ: In His divinity: He is the mystery of God, and in Him all the fullness of the entire Godhead the Father, the Son, and the Spirit dwells bodily.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>He comes in the name of the Father and works also in the name of the Father.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>His name is called the Eternal Father.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>He is the image of God to declare God.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In His name the Father sends the Holy Spirit, and in His name also the Holy Spirit comes.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>He sends the Holy Spirit from and with the Father, and the Holy Spirit also comes from and with the Father.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>He is the Spirit.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>He is the One who fills all in all.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>In His humanity: He became flesh, partaking of blood and flesh and taking the likeness of the flesh of sin.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>He became a man.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>He is the Firstborn of all creation.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>He is the Firstborn from the dead.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>He became the life-giving Spirit in resurrection.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The Spirit of God became His Spirit, the Spirit of Jesus Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>He poured out the Holy Spirit whom He had received from the Father, and He gives the Spirit not by measure.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>He was begotten with His humanity in resurrection to be the firstborn Son of God with many brothers.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>He was made both Lord and Christ in ascension.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>He is the Heir of all things.</S>
   </TEXT>
